On a hunting trip this August, Donald Trump Jr. shot and killed one.
Trump Jr. received special treatment during his summer trip, according to records obtained by ProPublica as well as interviews with people involved in the hunt.
Trump Jr. dressed in traditional Mongolian garb with Jandos Kontorbai Ahat, a member of the Mongolian president’s political party.
In the statement from Trump Jr.’s spokesman, he said that protection details are determined by the Secret Service, not Trump Jr. Trump Jr.’s spokesman did not comment on who accompanied the president’s son.
A spokeswoman for the service wouldn’t say whether Trump Jr. had applied for such a license.